reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Read this before you buy a Joby
reviews.reviewText: The Joby GorillaPod, a.k.a. "bendy tripod," looks retro-robot cool with its sectioned ball and socket legs. Yet, it's that ball and socket construction that is its undoing. While looking for some kind of bendy tripod, I was almost sold on the Joby until I read review after review about how it loses its strength after a while, and that makes perfect sense; anything with that number of friction fit pieces is doomed to wear out, such is the nature of friction.Enter the ULANZI MT-33 "octopus" tripod. It does away with the ball/socket sections in favor of high elastic rubber legs, meaning (like the Joby) it can be formed to fit around posts, branches, uneven surfaces, etc. to hold your phone or smaller DSLR or mirrorless exactly where you want.Add in the excellent ball head, side-mounted cold shoe, capability to mount a camera or phone - with another cold shoe above the phone, 1/4" screw mount on the other side, and built-in level, and you have the most complete package for vlogging you could want. That its price is half that of a Joby makes buying the ULANZI MT-33 a no-brainer.It's built far better than one would expect for the price, and is made from quality materials. This will be part of my kit wherever I go.Well done, ULANZI! I have one of your little lights for vlogging, too. It came with a magnetic diffuser and a number of gels, along with color temperature and brightness adjustments. It's a great light and is a perfect compliment to the MT-33.When it's time to shop for more vlogging gear or bits and pieces, ULANZI will be my first (and likely, last) place to start.
